title: fanoutqa: Identify the presidents of the United States who served two terms and their respective political affiliations. (ca085ff48e269f74)

chat_history.content: Identify the presidents of the United States who served two terms and their respective political affiliations.

Here is a list of the United States presidents who served two full terms, along with their political parties:

1. George Washington (1789-1797) - Independent
2. Thomas Jefferson (1801-1809) - Democratic-Republican
3. James Madison (1809-1817) - Democratic-Republican
4. James Monroe (1817-1825) - Democratic-Republican
5. Andrew Jackson (1829-1837) - Democratic
6. Ulysses S. Grant (1869-1877) - Republican
7. Grover Cleveland (non-consecutive terms: 1885-1889 and 1893-1897) - Democratic
8. Woodrow Wilson (1913-1921) - Democratic
9. Franklin D. Roosevelt (1933-1945) - Democratic
10. Dwight D. Eisenhower (1953-1961) - Republican
11. Ronald Reagan (1981-1989) - Republican
12. Bill Clinton (1993-2001) - Democratic
13. George W. Bush (2001-2009) - Republican
14. Barack Obama (2009-2017) - Democratic

It's worth noting that Franklin D. Roosevelt was the only president elected to more than two terms, but he died shortly into his fourth term.
